(Sciperaceae) and abundant grass in the shores (
Cognato & Fialho 2006
). Throughout its distribution it is usually abundant in the roots of dense beds of floating water hyacinths (

Eichornia crassipes

). Reproductive cycle extends from November to March (
Cognato & Fialho 2006
).
